(23, 697, '1609443419.jpg', 'Dominic', 'Ross-Hurst', 'Milton Keynes Tennis Club, Letchworth Sports and tennis club', 'LTA level 4, PTR Pro', 'I\'ve been playing tennis my whole life and have been coaching for 17 years.\r\n\r\nAs a player I\'ve competed in national and international pro events, achieving a world ranking at the age of 24. \r\n\r\nAs a coach I\'ve worked at numerous clubs and have been lucky enough to work with some fantastic junior performance players nationally and abroad.\r\n\r\nI now run both Milton Keynes Tennis Club and Letchworth Tennis Club coaching programmes and am the founder and director of DRH Sports.', '2020-12-31 19:36:59', '2020-12-31 20:24:57'),
(24, 707, NULL, 'Steven', 'Sumpter', 'Milton Keynes Tennis Club', 'LTA Level 3', 'I have been playing a wide range of sports since the age of 5 but specialised in tennis from the age of 15. I started coaching soon afterwards and now have 16 years coaching experience in clubs throughout MK but have been playing at Milton Keynes tennis club throughout that time.\r\nI have represented both Milton Keynes tennis club and Bucks men\'s County team at County and national level.\r\n\r\nI have coached both junior and adult players from all levels from beginner to national level and love coaching at the club. \r\n\r\nI am also the head coach at Swanbourne House school but you will see me at the club most evenings. If you see me at the club and have any questions please feel to ask.', '2021-01-01 12:00:49', '2021-01-01 12:00:49'),
(25, 765, NULL, 'Madeleine', 'Hyde', 'Letchworth Sports and Tennis Club', 'CC Level 3', '', '2021-01-02 11:41:35', '2021-01-02 11:41:35'),
(26, 813, '1609612030.jpeg', 'Caitlin', 'Ashman', 'Milton Keynes Tennis Club', 'Level 2 tennis coach', 'Im a full-time tennis coach and have been coaching at MKTC for over a year now but I have coached at a different club before coming to MKTC. \r\n\r\nI am a level 2 tennis coach and I am looking at doing my level 3 very soon. I have played county tennis for a couple of years representing Bedfordshire. Ive been playing tennis since I was 4 and still enjoy playing and coaching, I have experience in disability sessions and am open to all ages and abilities. \r\n\r\nMy belief is that tennis is a sport for everyone all ages and all abilities, in my sessions I try to make sure all the kids enjoy themselves but also learn at the same time. The most important part for me as a coach is they have fun and enjoy it.', '2021-01-02 18:27:10', '2021-01-02 18:55:31'),
(27, 829, '1609634138.jpeg', 'Justin', 'Philpott', 'Milton Keynes Tennis Club', 'LTA Level 3', 'I started playing Tennis at the age of 6 and I have played ever since, competing in tournaments across Ireland. \r\nI have attended Tennis Academys in Barcelona and at 16 I was accepted into the Sutton Junior Tennis Academy. \r\n\r\nI began coaching when I was 14 assisting coaches at my local tennis club.\r\nI have been coaching at MKTC for almost 2 years now coaching players of all ages and abilities helping them improve each session.', '2021-01-03 00:35:38', '2021-01-03 00:35:38'),
