trainers,&nbsp;ideally ones specific to tennis, no heelys, flip-flops or sandals. Long hair should be tied back.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease note, we do not hold spare clothing at the tennis club.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>WhatsApp Group:</strong></u>&nbsp;We will use the telephone number attached to the account used to make the booking. If this is not the correct number, please inform us by email to tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to do if you can&#39;t attend a class:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you are unable to attend the class and you want to make up the session you will need to contact the Head Coach&nbsp;<u><strong>BEFORE&nbsp;</strong></u>the session is missed. Classes can be made up at a later stage in the term provided you let the Head Coach know at least 24 hours prior to the missed class and that there is available space in the class you intend to join. Missed classes must be made up within the intended term and cannot be carried over to future terms or be held in credit for other participants, camps or courses.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Moving up to the next level:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">We endeavour to progress each player in our programme at the right stage for them. If this means that they need to be moved up mid term, then we&#39;ll do this. As a general rule of thumb, our goal is to get all CLUB group players to a stage where they can rally not only with a coach, but with another player of the same age from the back of the court. Once this is achieved, then we&#39;ll look to move the player up to the next level and will recommend competition play.</font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">There is no substitute&nbsp;for regular play. The best way to improve and progress is to play more often. Those who attend multiple coaching classes and have 1to1 lessons will improve the fastest. If you&#39;re interested in attending more than one coaching class per week, starting 1to1 lessons or have any questions about your or your child&#39;s development then please speak with your group class coach.</font></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Individual lessons:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Our DRH Sports tennis coaches offer 1to1 lessons for all those who want to take their development to the next level. Whilst the groups classes are essential for learning not only the basics in technique and tactics, every player is different, and therefore will have different requirements. 1to1 lessons give our team the opportunity to work more closely with players and give them bespoke advice and instruction that will enable their game to improve more quickly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe recommend that all players look at getting some 1to1 lessons at some point in their tennis journey so if this is something that interests you, please speak with your session coach or email tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Feedback:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font face="helvetica neue, helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif"><font style="font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At DRH Sports we rely on feedback from players and parents in order for us to grow and improve. We regularly send out feedback surveys throughout the terms but if you have comments about any part of the DRH Sports tennis coaching experience then please let us know by clicking the button below.</font></font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">If you love what we do, why not write a testimonial! Our testimonials go up on our website and helps others feel confident in joining us.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://49.249.236.30:8654/dominic-new/contact"><strong><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">Leave Feedback</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Useful Contacts:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>For programme&nbsp;enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;please contact us at tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk / 07901903520<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For website enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact info@drhsports.co.uk<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For urgent programme issues -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact Head Coach Dominic Ross-Hurst at 07929 341226</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Player1', 99, '', '<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>How to book this course: </strong></span><br />\r\n- Please select the person within your account that you wish to enrol on the course.<br />\r\n- If the persons name does not appear, please check their DOB is correct for this course.<br />\r\n- Only those people listed within your account with the correct DOB will show in the drop down list.&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Only tennis club members can book this course. Please ensure that the participant is a member before attending the first session. You can register for tennis club membership <a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join">HERE</a>.</p>', 133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '2021-04-30', 1, '2020-12-11 06:01:48', '2020-12-17 13:45:40'),
(52, 'mk-red-club-3-sat-10-11am', '<p style="text-align: center;">This <strong>Mini Tots</strong>&nbsp;coaching course is for children aged 3-4&nbsp;years old who are in the first stages of their tennis development.</p>', 'MK - Mini Tots - Sat 9.15-10am', 14, '156', 1, '162', 4, 1, 'Beginner', '1607686786.png', '', 'Jan 9th, 16th, 23th, 30th. Feb 6th, 13th, 27th. Mar 6th, 13th, 20th, 27th.', 'Mini Tots will be held at St Paul\'s Catholic School, Phoenix Dr, Leadenhall, Milton Keynes MK6 5EN', 'Saturday 9.15-10am', '3 - 4', '12', '<p><strong>Term begins</strong>: Week commencing Jan&nbsp;4th and runs for 11 weeks<br />\r\n<strong>Session Dates:&nbsp;</strong>Jan 9th, 16th, 23th, 30th. Feb 6th, 13th, 27th. Mar 6th, 13th, 20th, 27th.<br />\r\nThere will be no coaching during half term (Feb&nbsp;15th - 21st&nbsp;2021)&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:10.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span arial="" style="font-family:"><span style="color:#555555">In our <strong>Mini Tots</strong> sessions we give the players an introduction to tennis through fun games and exercises designed to develop co-ordination and athletic ability.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n<span style="font-size:10.5pt"><span arial="" style="font-family:"><span style="color:#555555"><span style="background:white">All the equipment and rackets will be provided by the club.</span><br />\r\n<span style="background:white">Parents may be required to accompany their child on court at the beginning, if the coach deems it necessary.</span><br />\r\n<span style="background:white">Throughout the term we will teach your child how to swing their racket correctly for a forehand, backhand and volley. For our most advanced tots we will start to work on movement to the ball, before stopping and playing their shot, and recovery to a central position.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To sign up for MKTC membership, please click <a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join" target="_blank"><strong>HERE</strong></a></p>', '<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Term Dates:</strong></span><span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Term begins - </strong>Monday January 4th 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Half Term - </strong>Monday February 15th - Sunday February 21st 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Term Ends - </strong>Sunday March 28th&nbsp;2021</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><b>Tennis Club Membership:</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">All courses with the exception of Mini Tots require tennis club membership. Please click&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join" target="_blank">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong>to join via the tennis club&#39;s website. If you are new to our tennis coaching programme at MKTC then you&#39;ll need to join.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Click&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://mcusercontent.com/ebd81016927d6a6233845eb5e/files/2f456447-6c59-4ca5-92bf-a2619c1f36e1/New_membership_guide_2020_2021.pdf" target="_blank">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong>for a guide on how to join Milton Keynes Tennis Club.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Session Locations:&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="color:#c0392b;">Mini Tots will be held at St Paul&#39;s Catholic School<br />\r\n<strong>Phoenix Dr, Leadenhall, Milton Keynes MK6 5EN</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE: </strong>We are currently in tier 4, which stipulates no indoor tennis can take place. If we have been given confirmation that we will be in Tier 4 by January 4<sup>th</sup>, all indoor sessions will be moved outdoors to Milton Keynes Tennis Club, MK6 3EA. As soon as we can go back indoors, we will.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If we are put into a period of &lsquo;Lockdown&rsquo; all group tennis sessions will be suspended.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please keep an eye on updates via email, Whatsapp and Facebook. We will keep you informed as to what is happening as promptly as we can.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Rackets and Equipment:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>RACKETS&nbsp;</strong>- All players need to bring their own tennis racket to sessions unless it is your first time.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you&#39;d like to buy a racket, we offer a selection of mini, junior and adult rackets which can be purchased from us. Just speak to your group coach for more information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>MEDICAL EQUIPMENT&nbsp;</strong>- If you or your child has a medical condition which requires equipment such as inhalers then we ask that they are brought to each class. Failure to bring medical equipment to the class may result in you or your child not being able to participate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Drop offs and picks ups:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">The following applies to parents of children booked on to coaching groups only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Drop offs -</strong></u>&nbsp;Please make sure that you accompany your child to the court or area that the class is taking place when dropping your child off and make sure that the coach is present and acknowledges taking your child into their care.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Pick ups -</strong></u>&nbsp;We can only allow a child leave our care when we see their parent so please make sure that you come into the tennis club or venue to meet them and the coach.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp;Parents of children within our Tots and Mini Red groups are required to stay on site throughout the duration of the class.&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Tennis club etiquette and safety:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Milton Keynes Tennis Club has a slightly unusual layout compared to most other tennis clubs. This is because our two entrances are at either end of the courts, which means that you have to walk across one court to get to another. This means that there is a risk of games and matches being interrupted by people walking at the back of courts or even the potential of people being hit by tennis balls.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMilton Keynes Tennis Club asks that all players and parents stop and wait the play to finish and for acknowledgement by those playing before walking behind the tennis courts.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>The weather and cancellations:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">We always try our best to run all classes regardless of the weather conditions, however there may be times when the weather conditions mean that it&#39;s unsuitable or unsafe to run the class. If this is the case, we may need to cancel the class.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf there is a cancellation you will be notified no less than 15 minutes&nbsp;before the lesson via WhatsApp and social media. Any lesson that is&nbsp;cancelled by us can be made up by the participant by attending any of our other classes that run that term.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf we are more than 15 minutes into the lesson and the weather becomes unsuitable, the session is deemed to have started and no makeup session will be provided.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn some cases, we may arrange a make up class for cancelled classes. These classes will be made up at a time that is suitable for the coach.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Communication:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">It&#39;s important that we have the ability to communicate quickly and easily with the players (or parents of) within our coaching groups. If sessions do need to be cancelled or if we need to notify you of upcoming events or changes then we will contact you via a WhatsApp group we will create for your session.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease make sure that you are added to the coaching session WhatsApp group if you haven&#39;t been by the second week of the term.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp;</u>The WhatsApp groups are used solely for communicating tennis club/coaching club matters and are not used by coaches, players or parents for any other reason.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to Wear:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Players should wear comfortable clothing appropriate for the weather conditions, and wear comfortable trainers,&nbsp;ideally ones specific to tennis, no heelys, flip-flops or sandals. Long hair should be tied back.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease note, we do not hold spare clothing at the tennis club.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>WhatsApp Group:</strong></u>&nbsp;We will use the telephone number attached to the account used to make the booking. If this is not the correct number, please inform us by email to tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to do if you can&#39;t attend a class:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you are unable to attend the class and you want to make up the session you will need to contact the Head Coach&nbsp;<u><strong>BEFORE&nbsp;</strong></u>the session is missed. Classes can be made up at a later stage in the term provided you let the Head Coach know at least 24 hours prior to the missed class and that there is available space in the class you intend to join. Missed classes must be made up within the intended term and cannot be carried over to future terms or be held in credit for other participants, camps or courses.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Moving up to the next level:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">We endeavour to progress each player in our programme at the right stage for them. If this means that they need to be moved up mid term, then we&#39;ll do this. As a general rule of thumb, our goal is to get all CLUB group players to a stage where they can rally not only with a coach, but with another player of the same age from the back of the court. Once this is achieved, then we&#39;ll look to move the player up to the next level and will recommend competition play.</font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">There is no substitute&nbsp;for regular play. The best way to improve and progress is to play more often. Those who attend multiple coaching classes and have 1to1 lessons will improve the fastest. If you&#39;re interested in attending more than one coaching class per week, starting 1to1 lessons or have any questions about your or your child&#39;s development then please speak with your group class coach.</font></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Individual lessons:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Our DRH Sports tennis coaches offer 1to1 lessons for all those who want to take their development to the next level. Whilst the groups classes are essential for learning not only the basics in technique and tactics, every player is different, and therefore will have different requirements. 1to1 lessons give our team the opportunity to work more closely with players and give them bespoke advice and instruction that will enable their game to improve more quickly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe recommend that all players look at getting some 1to1 lessons at some point in their tennis journey so if this is something that interests you, please speak with your session coach or email tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Feedback:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font face="helvetica neue, helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif"><font style="font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At DRH Sports we rely on feedback from players and parents in order for us to grow and improve. We regularly send out feedback surveys throughout the terms but if you have comments about any part of the DRH Sports tennis coaching experience then please let us know by clicking the button below.</font></font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">If you love what we do, why not write a testimonial! Our testimonials go up on our website and helps others feel confident in joining us.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://49.249.236.30:8654/dominic-new/contact"><strong><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">Leave Feedback</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Useful Contacts:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>For programme&nbsp;enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;please contact us at tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk / 07901903520<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For website enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact info@drhsports.co.uk<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For urgent programme issues -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact Head Coach Dominic Ross-Hurst at 07929 341226</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Player1', 86, '', '<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>How to book this course: </strong></span><br />\r\n- Please select the person within your account that you wish to enrol on the course.<br />\r\n- If the persons name does not appear, please check their DOB is correct for this course.<br />\r\n- Only those people listed within your account with the correct DOB will show in the drop down list.&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Only tennis club members can book this course. Please ensure that the participant is a member before attending the first session. You can register for tennis club membership <a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join">HERE</a>.</p>', 133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '2021-04-30', 1, '2020-12-11 06:05:21', '2020-12-30 14:43:24');
INSERT INTO `courses` (`id`, `slug`, `description`, `title`, `season`, `type`, `account_id`, `subtype`, `course_category`, `set_course_type_default`, `level`, `image`, `age`, `session_date`, `location`, `day_time`, `age_group`, `booking_slot`, `more_info`, `info_email_content`, `player`, `price`, `early_birth_price`, `bottom_section`, `linked_coach`, `coach_cost`, `venue_cost`, `equipment_cost`, `other_cost`, `tax_cost`, `status`, `sort`, `end_date`, `membership_popup`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(53, 'mk-red-club-3-sat-10-11am-1', '<p style="text-align: center;">This <strong>Orange/Green Club 1</strong> coaching course is for children aged 8-10 years old who are in the beginner stage of their tennis development.</p>', 'MK - Orange/Green Club 3 - Sat 11am - 12pm', 14, '156', 1, '164', 4, 1, 'Beginner', '1607689885.png', '', 'Jan 9th, 16th, 23th, 30th. Feb 6th, 13th, 27th. Mar 6th, 13th, 20th, 27th.', 'Milton Keynes Tennis Club, Woughton on the Green, MK6 3EA', 'Saturday 11am - 12pm', '8 - 10', '12', '<p><strong>Term begins</strong>: Week commencing Jan&nbsp;4th and runs for 11 weeks<br />\r\n<strong>Session Dates:&nbsp;</strong>Jan 9th, 16th, 23th, 30th. Feb 6th, 13th, 27th. Mar 6th, 13th, 20th, 27th.<br />\r\nThere will be no coaching during half term (Feb&nbsp;15th - 21st&nbsp;2021)&nbsp;<br />\r\n- You&nbsp;<strong><u>MUST&nbsp;</u></strong>be a member of MKTC to join this class. See joining info below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In our <strong>Orange and Green Club</strong> groups we aim to teach our players the basics in a fun environment, with plenty of fun games to break up the learning.<br />\r\nThroughout a term we will cover the main four shots in tennis: forehand, backhand, serve and volley.<br />\r\nWe will mostly teach with basket feeding to enforce the players&#39; technique effectively but, as they progress, we will introduce rallying, which is a great way to get the players to work together to improve their tennis.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo sign up for MKTC membership, please click&nbsp;<a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join" target="_blank"><strong>HERE</strong></a></p>', '<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Term Dates:</strong></span><span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Term begins - </strong>Monday January 4th 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Half Term - </strong>Monday February 15th - Sunday February 21st 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Term Ends - </strong>Sunday March 28th&nbsp;2021</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><b>Tennis Club Membership:</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">All courses with the exception of Mini Tots require tennis club membership. Please click&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join" target="_blank">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong>to join via the tennis club&#39;s website. If you are new to our tennis coaching programme at MKTC then you&#39;ll need to join.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Click&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://mcusercontent.com/ebd81016927d6a6233845eb5e/files/2f456447-6c59-4ca5-92bf-a2619c1f36e1/New_membership_guide_2020_2021.pdf" target="_blank">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong>for a guide on how to join Milton Keynes Tennis Club.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Session Locations:&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="color:#c0392b;">All coaching classes will be held outdoors at:&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Milton Keynes Tennis Club, Woughton on the Green, MK6 3EA.&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\r\n<em>When you pull into Woughton Playing Fields, park in the first car park on your left and park in the small car park. This is where the tennis club entrance is located.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Rackets and Equipment:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>RACKETS&nbsp;</strong>- All players need to bring their own tennis racket to sessions unless it is your first time.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you&#39;d like to buy a racket, we offer a selection of mini, junior and adult rackets which can be purchased from us. Just speak to your group coach for more information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>MEDICAL EQUIPMENT&nbsp;</strong>- If you or your child has a medical condition which requires equipment such as inhalers then we ask that they are brought to each class. Failure to bring medical equipment to the class may result in you or your child not being able to participate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Drop offs and picks ups:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">The following applies to parents of children booked on to coaching groups only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Drop offs -</strong></u>&nbsp;Please make sure that you accompany your child to the court or area that the class is taking place when dropping your child off and make sure that the coach is present and acknowledges taking your child into their care.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Pick ups -</strong></u>&nbsp;We can only allow a child leave our care when we see their parent so please make sure that you come into the tennis club or venue to meet them and the coach.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp;Parents of children within our Tots and Mini Red groups are required to stay on site throughout the duration of the class.&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Tennis club etiquette and safety:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Milton Keynes Tennis Club has a slightly unusual layout compared to most other tennis clubs. This is because our two entrances are at either end of the courts, which means that you have to walk across one court to get to another. This means that there is a risk of games and matches being interrupted by people walking at the back of courts or even the potential of people being hit by tennis balls.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMilton Keynes Tennis Club asks that all players and parents stop and wait the play to finish and for acknowledgement by those playing before walking behind the tennis courts.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>The weather and cancellations:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">We always try our best to run all classes regardless of the weather conditions, however there may be times when the weather conditions mean that it&#39;s unsuitable or unsafe to run the class. If this is the case, we may need to cancel the class.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf there is a cancellation you will be notified no less than 15 minutes&nbsp;before the lesson via WhatsApp and social media. Any lesson that is&nbsp;cancelled by us can be made up by the participant by attending any of our other classes that run that term.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf we are more than 15 minutes into the lesson and the weather becomes unsuitable, the session is deemed to have started and no makeup session will be provided.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn some cases, we may arrange a make up class for cancelled classes. These classes will be made up at a time that is suitable for the coach.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Communication:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">It&#39;s important that we have the ability to communicate quickly and easily with the players (or parents of) within our coaching groups. If sessions do need to be cancelled or if we need to notify you of upcoming events or changes then we will contact you via a WhatsApp group we will create for your session.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease make sure that you are added to the coaching session WhatsApp group if you haven&#39;t been by the second week of the term.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp;</u>The WhatsApp groups are used solely for communicating tennis club/coaching club matters and are not used by coaches, players or parents for any other reason.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to Wear:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Players should wear comfortable clothing appropriate for the weather conditions, and wear comfortable trainers,&nbsp;ideally ones specific to tennis, no heelys, flip-flops or sandals. Long hair should be tied back.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease note, we do not hold spare clothing at the tennis club.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>WhatsApp Group:</strong></u>&nbsp;We will use the telephone number attached to the account used to make the booking. If this is not the correct number, please inform us by email to tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to do if you can&#39;t attend a class:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you are unable to attend the class and you want to make up the session you will need to contact the Head Coach&nbsp;<u><strong>BEFORE&nbsp;</strong></u>the session is missed. Classes can be made up at a later stage in the term provided you let the Head Coach know at least 24 hours prior to the missed class and that there is available space in the class you intend to join. Missed classes must be made up within the intended term and cannot be carried over to future terms or be held in credit for other participants, camps or courses.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Moving up to the next level:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">We endeavour to progress each player in our programme at the right stage for them. If this means that they need to be moved up mid term, then we&#39;ll do this. As a general rule of thumb, our goal is to get all CLUB group players to a stage where they can rally not only with a coach, but with another player of the same age from the back of the court. Once this is achieved, then we&#39;ll look to move the player up to the next level and will recommend competition play.</font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">There is no substitute&nbsp;for regular play. The best way to improve and progress is to play more often. Those who attend multiple coaching classes and have 1to1 lessons will improve the fastest. If you&#39;re interested in attending more than one coaching class per week, starting 1to1 lessons or have any questions about your or your child&#39;s development then please speak with your group class coach.</font></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Individual lessons:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Our DRH Sports tennis coaches offer 1to1 lessons for all those who want to take their development to the next level. Whilst the groups classes are essential for learning not only the basics in technique and tactics, every player is different, and therefore will have different requirements. 1to1 lessons give our team the opportunity to work more closely with players and give them bespoke advice and instruction that will enable their game to improve more quickly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe recommend that all players look at getting some 1to1 lessons at some point in their tennis journey so if this is something that interests you, please speak with your session coach or email tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Feedback:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font face="helvetica neue, helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif"><font style="font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At DRH Sports we rely on feedback from players and parents in order for us to grow and improve. We regularly send out feedback surveys throughout the terms but if you have comments about any part of the DRH Sports tennis coaching experience then please let us know by clicking the button below.</font></font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">If you love what we do, why not write a testimonial! Our testimonials go up on our website and helps others feel confident in joining us.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://49.249.236.30:8654/dominic-new/contact"><strong><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">Leave Feedback</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Useful Contacts:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>For programme&nbsp;enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;please contact us at tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk / 07901903520<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For website enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact info@drhsports.co.uk<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For urgent programme issues -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact Head Coach Dominic Ross-Hurst at 07929 341226</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Player1', 99, '', '<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>How to book this course: </strong></span><br />\r\n- Please select the person within your account that you wish to enrol on the course.<br />\r\n- If the persons name does not appear, please check their DOB is correct for this course.<br />\r\n- Only those people listed within your account with the correct DOB will show in the drop down list.&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Only tennis club members can book this course. Please ensure that the participant is a member before attending the first session. You can register for tennis club membership <a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join">HERE</a>.</p>', 133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '2021-04-30', 1, '2020-12-11 06:57:45', '2020-12-17 16:12:06'),
(54, 'mk-red-club-2-wed-5-6pm-2', '<p style="text-align: center;">This <strong>Yellow Club 2</strong>&nbsp;coaching course is for children aged 11-18&nbsp;years old who are in the beginner stage of their tennis development.</p>', 'MK - Yellow Club 2 - Wed 6-7pm', 14, '156', 1, '214', 4, 1, 'Beginner', '1607690578.png', '', 'Jan 6th, 13th, 20th, 27th. Feb 3rd, 10th, 24th. Mar 3rd, 10th, 17th, 24th.', 'Milton Keynes Tennis Club, Woughton on the Green, MK6 3EA', 'Wednesdays 6-7pm', '11 - 18', '12', '<p><strong>Term begins</strong>: Week commencing Jan&nbsp;4th and runs for 11 weeks<br />\r\n<strong>Session Dates:&nbsp;</strong>Jan 6th, 13th, 20th, 27th. Feb 3rd, 10th, 24th. Mar 3rd, 10th, 17th, 24th.<br />\r\nThere will be no coaching during half term (Feb&nbsp;15th - 21st&nbsp;2021)&nbsp;<br />\r\n- You&nbsp;<strong><u>MUST&nbsp;</u></strong>be a member of MKTC to join this class. See joining info below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In our <strong>Yellow Club</strong> groups we will work on all the basic shots in tennis: forehand, backhand, serve and volley. We will also cover the correct grips and the right path, angle, speed (PAS) for each shot.<br />\r\nAs the players progress they will start to learn the basic tactical situations in tennis and how to score and compete.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo sign up for MKTC membership, please click&nbsp;<a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join" target="_blank"><b>HERE</b></a></p>', '<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Term Dates:</strong></span><span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Term begins - </strong>Monday January 4th 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Half Term - </strong>Monday February 15th - Sunday February 21st 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Term Ends - </strong>Sunday March 28th&nbsp;2021</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><b>Tennis Club Membership:</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">All courses with the exception of Mini Tots require tennis club membership. Please click&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join" target="_blank">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong>to join via the tennis club&#39;s website. If you are new to our tennis coaching programme at MKTC then you&#39;ll need to join.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Click&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://mcusercontent.com/ebd81016927d6a6233845eb5e/files/2f456447-6c59-4ca5-92bf-a2619c1f36e1/New_membership_guide_2020_2021.pdf" target="_blank">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong>for a guide on how to join Milton Keynes Tennis Club.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Session Locations:&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="color:#c0392b;">All coaching classes will be held outdoors at:&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Milton Keynes Tennis Club, Woughton on the Green, MK6 3EA.&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\r\n<em>When you pull into Woughton Playing Fields, park in the first car park on your left and park in the small car park. This is where the tennis club entrance is located.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Rackets and Equipment:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>RACKETS&nbsp;</strong>- All players need to bring their own tennis racket to sessions unless it is your first time.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you&#39;d like to buy a racket, we offer a selection of mini, junior and adult rackets which can be purchased from us. Just speak to your group coach for more information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>MEDICAL EQUIPMENT&nbsp;</strong>- If you or your child has a medical condition which requires equipment such as inhalers then we ask that they are brought to each class. Failure to bring medical equipment to the class may result in you or your child not being able to participate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Drop offs and picks ups:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">The following applies to parents of children booked on to coaching groups only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Drop offs -</strong></u>&nbsp;Please make sure that you accompany your child to the court or area that the class is taking place when dropping your child off and make sure that the coach is present and acknowledges taking your child into their care.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Pick ups -</strong></u>&nbsp;We can only allow a child leave our care when we see their parent so please make sure that you come into the tennis club or venue to meet them and the coach.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp;Parents of children within our Tots and Mini Red groups are required to stay on site throughout the duration of the class.&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Tennis club etiquette and safety:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Milton Keynes Tennis Club has a slightly unusual layout compared to most other tennis clubs. This is because our two entrances are at either end of the courts, which means that you have to walk across one court to get to another. This means that there is a risk of games and matches being interrupted by people walking at the back of courts or even the potential of people being hit by tennis balls.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMilton Keynes Tennis Club asks that all players and parents stop and wait the play to finish and for acknowledgement by those playing before walking behind the tennis courts.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>The weather and cancellations:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">We always try our best to run all classes regardless of the weather conditions, however there may be times when the weather conditions mean that it&#39;s unsuitable or unsafe to run the class. If this is the case, we may need to cancel the class.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf there is a cancellation you will be notified no less than 15 minutes&nbsp;before the lesson via WhatsApp and social media. Any lesson that is&nbsp;cancelled by us can be made up by the participant by attending any of our other classes that run that term.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf we are more than 15 minutes into the lesson and the weather becomes unsuitable, the session is deemed to have started and no makeup session will be provided.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn some cases, we may arrange a make up class for cancelled classes. These classes will be made up at a time that is suitable for the coach.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Communication:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">It&#39;s important that we have the ability to communicate quickly and easily with the players (or parents of) within our coaching groups. If sessions do need to be cancelled or if we need to notify you of upcoming events or changes then we will contact you via a WhatsApp group we will create for your session.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease make sure that you are added to the coaching session WhatsApp group if you haven&#39;t been by the second week of the term.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp;</u>The WhatsApp groups are used solely for communicating tennis club/coaching club matters and are not used by coaches, players or parents for any other reason.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to Wear:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Players should wear comfortable clothing appropriate for the weather conditions, and wear comfortable trainers,&nbsp;ideally ones specific to tennis, no heelys, flip-flops or sandals. Long hair should be tied back.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease note, we do not hold spare clothing at the tennis club.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>WhatsApp Group:</strong></u>&nbsp;We will use the telephone number attached to the account used to make the booking. If this is not the correct number, please inform us by email to tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>What to do if you can&#39;t attend a class:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">If you are unable to attend the class and you want to make up the session you will need to contact the Head Coach&nbsp;<u><strong>BEFORE&nbsp;</strong></u>the session is missed. Classes can be made up at a later stage in the term provided you let the Head Coach know at least 24 hours prior to the missed class and that there is available space in the class you intend to join. Missed classes must be made up within the intended term and cannot be carried over to future terms or be held in credit for other participants, camps or courses.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Moving up to the next level:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">We endeavour to progress each player in our programme at the right stage for them. If this means that they need to be moved up mid term, then we&#39;ll do this. As a general rule of thumb, our goal is to get all CLUB group players to a stage where they can rally not only with a coach, but with another player of the same age from the back of the court. Once this is achieved, then we&#39;ll look to move the player up to the next level and will recommend competition play.</font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<font color="#000000"><font style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">There is no substitute&nbsp;for regular play. The best way to improve and progress is to play more often. Those who attend multiple coaching classes and have 1to1 lessons will improve the fastest. If you&#39;re interested in attending more than one coaching class per week, starting 1to1 lessons or have any questions about your or your child&#39;s development then please speak with your group class coach.</font></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Individual lessons:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;">Our DRH Sports tennis coaches offer 1to1 lessons for all those who want to take their development to the next level. Whilst the groups classes are essential for learning not only the basics in technique and tactics, every player is different, and therefore will have different requirements. 1to1 lessons give our team the opportunity to work more closely with players and give them bespoke advice and instruction that will enable their game to improve more quickly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe recommend that all players look at getting some 1to1 lessons at some point in their tennis journey so if this is something that interests you, please speak with your session coach or email tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Feedback:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><font color="#000000"><font face="helvetica neue, helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif"><font style="font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At DRH Sports we rely on feedback from players and parents in order for us to grow and improve. We regularly send out feedback surveys throughout the terms but if you have comments about any part of the DRH Sports tennis coaching experience then please let us know by clicking the button below.</font></font></font><br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<br style="color:#757575; font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:left; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial" />\r\n<span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">If you love what we do, why not write a testimonial! Our testimonials go up on our website and helps others feel confident in joining us.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://49.249.236.30:8654/dominic-new/contact"><strong><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="text-align: left; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="font-family:Helvetica"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-variant-caps:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="letter-spacing:normal"><span style="orphans:2"><span style="text-transform:none"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="widows:2"><span style="word-spacing:0px"><span style="background-color:#ffffff"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="color:#000000">Leave Feedback</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>Useful Contacts:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>For programme&nbsp;enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;please contact us at tenniscoaching@drhsports.co.uk / 07901903520<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For website enquiries -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact info@drhsports.co.uk<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>For urgent programme issues -&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;contact Head Coach Dominic Ross-Hurst at 07929 341226</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Player1', 99, '', '<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong>How to book this course: </strong></span><br />\r\n- Please select the person within your account that you wish to enrol on the course.<br />\r\n- If the persons name does not appear, please check their DOB is correct for this course.<br />\r\n- Only those people listed within your account with the correct DOB will show in the drop down list.&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Only tennis club members can book this course. Please ensure that the participant is a member before attending the first session. You can register for tennis club membership <a href="https://clubspark.lta.org.uk/MiltonKeynesTennisClub/Membership/Join">HERE</a>.</p>', 133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 14, '2021-04-30', 1, '2020-12-11 07:05:16', '2020-12-17 16:44:19');
